The paper deals with multi-user scheduling in a wireless communication system, which involves information and power transfer. This topic falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses fairness in scheduling, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper involves optimization and analysis of performance, which are topics in machine learning (cs.MM) and game theory (cs.GT).
